Melvins]]\n| cover      = Pinkus_Abortion_Technician_(2018)_cover.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = April 20, 2018\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     = Sound of Sirens Studio\n| genre      = [[Alternative rock]], [[Southern rock]], [[psychedelic rock]], [[experimental rock]]\n| length     = 37:05\n| label      = [[Ipecac Recordings|Ipecac]]\n| producer   = The Melvins\n| prev_title = [[A Walk with Love & Death]]\n| prev_year  = 2017\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n}}\n\n'''''Pinkus Abortion Technician''''' is the 23rd album (not including split albums) by the [[Melvins]] released on April 20, 2018 through [[Ipecac Recordings]]. It features both \"ongoing\" bass player [[Steven Shane McDonald|Steven McDonald]] and \"occasional bottom ender\" [[Jeff Pinkus]],<ref name=\"Bandcamp\">{{cite web |url=https://melvinsofficial.bandcamp.com/album/pinkus-abortion-technician |title=Pinkus Abortion Technician |accessdate=April 20, 2018 |work=Bandcamp}}</ref> who receives writing credit on four of the album's five original songs. The title is a direct reference to the [[Butthole Surfers]] third album ''[[Locust Abortion Technician]]''.\n\n{{Album ratings\n| MC        = 66/100<ref name=\"MC1\">{{cite web|title=Pinkus Abortion Technician by Melvins|url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/pinkus-abortion-technician/melvins|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=April 27, 2018}}</ref>\n| rev1      = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1score = {{rating|3.5|5}}<ref name=\"allmusic1\">{{cite web|last1=Deming|first1=Mark|title=Melvins \u2013 Pinkus Abortion Technician|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/pinkus-abortion-technician-mw0003152248|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=April 27, 2018}}</ref>\n|rev2 = ''[[Exclaim!]]''\n|rev2score = 7/10<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/the_melvins-pinkus_abortion_technician|title=The Melvins Pinkus Abortion Technician|website=exclaim.ca}}</ref>\n|rev3 = Punknews.org\n|rev3score = {{rating|4|5}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.punknews.org/