{"title_page": "Russ (UK rapper)", "text_new": "{{distinguish|Russ (rapper)}}\n{{short description|British rapper}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Russ\n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = <!-- Please do not add with a reliable source!-->\n| alias            = Russ Splash, Russ BattyMan, RussMB\n| birth_place      = [[Lewisham]], [[London]], England<ref name=\"shortlist\"/>\n| genre            = [[UK drill]]\n| years_active     = 2016\u2013present\n| instrument       = Vocals\n| label            = [[Virgin Records]]\n| associated_acts  = {{hlist|Taze|SMG|Digga D||Loski|[[Pressa (rapper)|Pressa]]}} \n| website        = \n}}\n\n'''Russ''', also known as '''Russ Splash''', '''RussMB''' or '''Russ Millions''', is a British rapper and songwriter.<ref name=\"shortlist\">{{cite web |title=This is the viral dance craze of the year you need to know about |url=https://www.shortlist.com/entertainment/music/viral-dance-craze-2019-russ-gun-lean/379188 |website=[[ShortList]] |accessdate=9 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402145547/https://www.shortlist.com/entertainment/music/viral-dance-craze-2019-russ-gun-lean/379188 |archive-date=2 April 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> In December 2018 he released his [[Single (music)|single]] \"Gun Lean\" on [[Virgin Records]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=McQuaid |first1=Ian |title=UK Driller Russ Is Here to Stay \u2013 and to Make You Dance |url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_uk/article/pa5j58/russ-splash-gun-lean-dance-interview-2019 |website=Noisey |publisher=[[Vice (magazine)|Vice]] |accessdate=9 March 2019 |date=15 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402162435/https://noisey.vice.com/en_uk/article/pa5j58/russ-splash-gun-lean-dance-interview-2019 |archive-date=2 April 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The track peaked at number 9 on the [[UK Singles Chart]],<ref name=\"UKchart\"/> becoming the second [[Drill music#UK drill|UK drill]] track to reach the top 10.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hancox |first1=Dan |title=Skengdo and AM: the drill rappers sentenced for playing their song |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/jan/31/skengdo-and-am-the-drill-rappers-sentenced-for-playing-their-song |website=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=9 March 2019 |date=31 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190809083127/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/jan/31/skengdo-and-am-the-drill-rappers-sentenced-for-playing-their-song |archive-date=9 August 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe dance that Russ performs in the [[music video]] became a \"dance craze\" and was mimicked by [[Football player|footballers]] including [[Jesse Lingard]].<ref>{{cite web |title=What is the \u2018gun lean\u2019? Jesse Lingard\u2019s celebration mimics drill dance craze |url=https://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/entertainment/music/news/what-is-the-gun-lean-jesse-lingards-celebration-mimics-drill-dance-craze-37653450.html |website=[[Belfast Telegraph]] |accessdate=9 March 2019 |date=23 December 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331192825/https://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/entertainment/music/news/what-is-the-gun-lean-jesse-lingards-celebration-mimics-drill-dance-craze-37653450.html |archive-date=31 March 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> It was ranked by ''[[The Guardian]]'' at number 10 on their list of \"greatest pop music dance crazes\".<ref>{{cite web |last=Snapes |first=Laura |title=The greatest pop music dance crazes \u2013 ranked! |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/jan/04/the-greatest-pop-music-dance-crazes-ranked |website=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=9 March 2019 |date=4 January 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190309193432/https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/jan/04/the-greatest-pop-music-dance-crazes-ranked |archive-date=9 March 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn April 2019 his follow-up single \"Keisha & Becky\" with Tion Wayne entered the UK Singles Chart at number 19, and later peaked at number seven. Which later become BPI platinum certified. <ref name=\"UKchart\"/>\n\n==Discography==\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of singles as lead artist, with selected chart positions, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Certifications\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[UK Singles Chart|UK]]<br /><ref name=\"UKchart\">{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/51551/russ/|title=RUSS - full Official Charts History|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=17 May 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402182842/https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/51551/russ/|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Irish Singles Chart|IRE]]<br /><ref name=\"Irishchart\">Peak positions in Ireland: \n* For \"Gun Lean\": {{cite web|url=http://irma.ie/index.cfm?page=irish-charts&chart=Singles|title=IRMA \u2013 Irish Charts|publisher=[[Irish Recorded Music Association]]|accessdate=17 May 2019|format=To access, go to \"2019\" > \"01-Feb-19\" and filter by \"Russ\"|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181226125524/http://www.irma.ie/index.cfm?page=irish-charts&chart=Singles|archive-date=26 December 2018|url-status=live}}\n* For \"Keisha & Becky\": {{cite web|url=http://irma.ie/index.cfm?page=irish-charts&chart=Singles|title=IRMA \u2013 Irish Charts|publisher=Irish Recorded Music Association|accessdate=17 May 2019|format=To access, go to \"2019\" > \"19-Apr-19\" and filter by \"Russ\"|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181226125524/http://www.irma.ie/index.cfm?page=irish-charts&chart=Singles|archive-date=26 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Trick or Treat\